1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
01) PURPOSE :
    -------
0   COPY SEQUENTIAL DATSETS PERFORMING MULTIPLE COPY OPERATIONS
    IN ONE JOB STEP.
0   CREATE AN OUTPUT FILE WHICH CONTAINS PARTITIONED DATA
    SET MEMBERS (I.E. PROCEDURES OR CONTROL CARDS) COPIED
    FROM THE BRUSSELS CENTRAL COMPUTER.  THIS GIVES A
    POSSIBILITY TO CREATE INSTREAM PROCEDURES.
0   THIS PROGRAM IS USED IN PROCEDURE 'STLJOBS' WHICH COLLECTS
    ALL JOBS TO BE SUBMITTED TO ST. LOUIS COMPUTER.
1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
02)  LIMITATIONS :
    -----------
0   2.1. ONLY SEQUENTIAL DATA SET MAY BE PROCESSED.
    2.2. ONLY FIXED LENGTH RECORDS MAY BE PROCESSED.
    2.3. PROCEDURES TO BE COPIED MUST BE A MEMBER OF A SINGLE
         PARTITIONED DATA SET,CONCATENATION IS NOT ADVISED.
1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
03) INPUT :
    -----
0   3.1. DDNAME SYSUT1 :
         -------------
0        MANDATORY INPUT SEQUENTIAL DATA SET.  ALL RECORDS
         OTHER THAN UT496 CONTROL CARDS ARE COPIED, UNCHANGED,
         ON SYSUT2 AND SYSUT3 OUTPUT DATA SETS.  CONTROL
         RECORDS ARE REPLACED BY THE PROCEDURES SPECIFIED
         IN THE RECORD.
         THE SYSUT1 DATA SET MAY BE ON TAPE, DISK, CARDS OR
         ANY DEVICE SUPPORTED BY QSAM.  IF STANDARD LABELS ARE
         PROVIDED, THERE IS NO NEED TO SPECIFY DCB PARAMETERS.
         TWO OR MORE DATA SETS MAY BE COMBINED BY CONCATENATION
         AND MAY BE ON UNLIKE DEVICE TYPES IF SO REQUESTED IN
         THE EXEC CARD.  NORMAL RULES OF CONCATENATION APPLY.
0   3.2. DDNAME SYSLIB :
         -------------
0        OPTIONAL PARTITIONED DATA SET.  MANDATORY IF AN INPUT
         CONTROL CARD IS TO BE REPLACED BY A PARTITIONED DATA
         SET MEMBER.  IN THIS CASE, THE SYSLIB CARD MUST SPECIFY
         THE LIBRARY NAME IN WHICH THE PDS MEMBER TO BE COPIED
         IS AVAILABLE.  CONCATENATION OF LIBRARIES IS INADVISABLE.
0   3.3. ANY DDNAME
         ----------
0        OPTIONAL INPUT SEQUENTIAL DATASET (OR PDS MEMBER) TO BE
         SPECIFIED IN A .*DDN CONTROL CARD.
1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
04)  OUTPUT :
    ------
0   4.1. DDNAME SYSPRINT :
         ---------------
0        OPTIONAL MESSAGE DATA SET CONTAINING THE FOLLOWING :
         - A LIST OF ALL THE UT496 CONTROL CARDS SUBMITTED
           IN SYSUT1 INPUT FILE.
         - A WARNING ERROR MESSAGE IF THE REQUESTED PROCEDURE
           IS NOT FOUND.
         - THE STATUS OF THE VARIOUS DATA SETS, AND THE NUMBER
           OF RECORDS READ FROM OR WRITE TO.
         - THE RETURN CODE.
0   4.2. DDNAME SYSUT2 :
         -------------
0        OBLIGATORY SEQUENTIAL DATA SET CONTAINING THE
         FOLLOWING :
         - A COPY OF THE INPUT DATA SET EXCLUDING UT496
           CONTROL CARDS.
         - '/*PROC' CONTROL RECORDS ARE REPLACED BY THE PROCE-
           DURE REQUESTED (IF FOUND IN LIBRARIES SPECIFIED IN
           SYSLIB), AND A '//PEND' DELIMITER.
         - '.*MEMB' CONTROL RECORDS ARE REPLACED BY THE
           PARTITIONED DATA SET MEMBER REQUESTED (IF FOUND
           IN LIBRARIES SPECIFIED IN SYSLIB).
         - '.*DDN' CONTROL CARDS ARE REPLACED BY THE SPECIFIED
           SEQUENTIAL DATASET (WHICH MAY BE ONE MEMBER OF A PDS).
           OPTIONALLY THE INPUT FILE IS WRITTEN TO ANOTHER
           USER SPECIFIED DDNAME.
         - IF 'INTRDR' PARAMETER IS SPECIFIED IN THE EXEC CARD,
           A '/*EOF' CARD IS ADDED AT THE END OF OUTPUTS DATA
           SETS IN ORDER TO ALLOW DIRECT INPUT THROUGHT INTERNAL
           READER.
         - DCB PARAMETERS NEED NOT BE QUOTED IF THEY ARE THE
           SAME AS FOR THE INPUT DATA SET.
         - IF 'INTRDR' PARAMETER IS SPECIFIED, OUTPUT DCB'S ARE
           FORCED TO FIXED, LRECL 80, BLKSIZE 80, AND BUFNO=1.
0   4.3. DDNAME SYSUT3 :
         -------------
0        SAME AS SYSUT2 BUT OPTIONAL.
0   4.4. ANY DDNAME :
         ----------
0        OPTIONAL OUTPUT SEQUENTIAL DATASET (OR PDS MEMBER) TO
         BE SPECIFIED BY A PARM FIELD OF 'DDNAME=' OR IN A .*DDN
         CONTROL CARD.
1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
05) OPERATION :
    ---------
0   5.1. CONTROL RECORDS :
         ---------------
0        THE FORMAT OF SYSUT1 CONTROL RECORDS WHICH INVOKE
         THE COPY OF PARTITIONED DATA SET MEMBERS IS :
         /*PROC B NNNNNNNN(,NNNNNNNN)
         .*MEMB B NNNNNNNN(,NNNNNNNN)
         WHERE :
         /*PROC =  KEY WORD (COL. 1 TO 6) IDENTIFYING THE COPY
         .*MEMB =  KEY WORD (COL. 1 TO 6) IDENTIFYING THE COPY
         B      =  ONE OR MORE BLANKS.
         NNNNNNNN = NAME OF THE PDS MEMBERS TO BE COPIED.
0        THE FORMAT OF SYSUT1 CONTROL RECORDS WHICH INVOKE THE
         COPY OF SEQUENTIAL DATASETS IS :
        .*DDN BB IIIIIIII<,DDNAME=OOOOOOOO>
         WHERE :
         .*DDN = KEYWORD (COL 1 TO 5)IDENTIFYING THE COPY
         IIIIIIII = DDNAME OF JCL CARD SPECIFYING INPUT DATASET.
         DDNAME=    IS A KEYWORD INDICATING THAT THE OUTPUT IS NOT TO
                    SYSUT2,BUT TO A USER SPECIFIED DDNAME.
         OOOOOOOO = USER OUTPUT DD CARD NAME.
         BB       = TWO OR MORE BLANKS
0   5.2. EXEC PARAMETER :
         --------------
0        UNLIKE :  INDICATES SYSUT1 INPUT CONCATENATED ON UNLIKE DEVICES
         NODUMP :  POSSIBILITY TO SUPPRESS THE PROGRAM DUMP.
         INTRDR :  AN '/*EOF' CARD IS ADDED AT THE END OF OUTPUT
         DDNAME=:  SPECIFIES DDNAME OF OUTPUT DATASET TO BE USED IN
                   PLACE OF SYSUT2.
         LINKLIB:  SPECIFIES THAT EVERY OUTPUT RECORD CONTAINING THE
                   CHARACTER STRING 'DSN=SYS2.LINKLIB' WILL BE MODIFIED
                   TO READ 'DSN=BXL.LINKLIB',THE LIBRARY OF BXL
                   UTILITIES ON THE ST.LOUIS SYSTEM.
0        NOTE : PARAMETERS ARE KEYWORDS AND NOT POSITIONAL.
         ----
1************
 * UT496    *
 ************
0   5.3. JCL :
         ---
         //STEPNAME     EXEC PGM=UT496,PARM='UNLIKE,NODUMP'
         //SYSPRINT     DD   SYSOUT=A
         //SYSLIB       DD   DSN=SYS2.STLPROCS,DISP=SHR
         //SYSUT1       DD   DSN=DSNAME,DISP=...
         //SYSUT2       DD   DSN=......,DISP=...,
         //             UNIT=...(,VOL=...)(,SPACE=...)
         //           (,LABEL=)(,DCB=...)
0        //SYSUT3       AS SYSUT2.
0        NOTE :-SYSUT2 AND SYSUT3 MAY SPECIFY SYSOUT=A,
